I've successfully generated the PlantUML component diagram for the Xen Performance Analysis Tool and saved it to `zeroShot_claude_plantumlcode/nikmis_xentrace-analysis.puml`.

The diagram focuses on deployment and data flow aspects, showing:

**Deployment Architecture:**
- Separation into logical layers (Main Controller, Data Capture, Core Processing, Analysis Tools)
- External components (Xen Hypervisor, xentrace process)
- Core processing components (Reader, EventHandler, Event structures)
- Modular analysis tool components
- Supporting infrastructure (common handlers, data structures)

**Data Flow:**
- Trace data capture from Xen Hypervisor through xentrace
- File-based data transfer to Reader
- Event parsing and buffering in memory
- Event distribution through EventHandler using observer pattern
- Parallel dispatch to multiple analysis tools
- Results output from each analysis component

The diagram uses proper PlantUML component syntax with ports, interfaces, and clear directional flows to illustrate the event-driven architecture and modular design of the system.
